# Supabase Configuration
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard (https://app.supabase.com)
# Project Settings > API

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here
NEXT_PUBLIC_KAKAO_MAP_APP_KEY=your-kakao-javascript-key-here

# Service Role Key (server-only, optional for future admin/server operations)
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

# ============================================
# Google OAuth Setup Instructions
# ============================================
#
# This project uses Google OAuth for authentication.
# Follow these steps to configure Google OAuth:
#
# 1. Google Cloud Console Setup (https://console.cloud.google.com)
#    - Create a new project or select existing one
#    - Enable Google OAuth consent screen for email/profile/openid scopes
#
# 2. Create OAuth 2.0 Credentials
#    - Go to: APIs & Services > Credentials
#    - Click "Create Credentials" > "OAuth client ID"
#    - Application type: "Web application"
#
# 3. Configure OAuth Consent Screen
#    - Add your app name and support email
#    - Add authorized domain (if using custom domain)
#    - Add scopes: email, profile, openid
#
# 4. Set Authorized JavaScript Origins
#    Development:
#      http://localhost:3000
#    Production:
#      https://gatitagachon.vercel.app
#
# 5. Set Authorized Redirect URIs
#    Use the Supabase callback URL:
#      https://your-project-id.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#
# 6. Supabase Dashboard Setup (https://app.supabase.com)
#    - Go to: Authentication > Providers
#    - Enable "Google"
#    - Paste your Google Client ID and Client Secret
#    - Save changes
#
# 7. Important Notes
#    - Only @gachon.ac.kr emails are allowed in app logic
#    - Keep Client Secret secure and never commit to git
#
# ============================================
